Class MapPane

  • java.lang.Object
    • javafx.scene.Node
      • javafx.scene.Parent
        • javafx.scene.layout.Region
          • javafx.scene.layout.Pane
            • controls.MapPane
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    javafx.css.Styleable, javafx.event.EventTarget

    public class MapPane
extends javafx.scene.layout.Pane
    MapPane is slightly modified JavaFX Pane class that implements zoom and dragging. All entities are displayed on this modified pane. In the Main class, this pane is referenced as 'mapCanvas'.
    Author:
    Michal Rein, Ondřej Motyčka

    • Constructor Detail

      • MapPane

        public MapPane()
        Constructor of MapPane. Scale class is passed to the pane entity, listener which observes changes of zoom factor value is set and drag event for map moving is implemented.

    • Method Detail

      • changeZoomFactor

        private void changeZoomFactor(java.lang.Number newValue)
        Set new X and Y axis scaling of the map, this can be done by modifying Scale class. Method requestLayout() is invoked to request render of changes.
        Parameters:
        newValue - New zoom factor value.

      • setZoomFactor

        public void setZoomFactor(java.lang.Number value)
        Set zoomFactor property value. This will be observed by listener that will call method to change overall scaling.
        Parameters:
        value - Value of zoom factor.
